from collections import defaultdict
import MeCab

# mecab 
tagger = MeCab.Tagger("-r ../tools/usr/local/etc/mecabrc --unk-feature ")

# 
word_counts = defaultdict(lambda: 0)

# 
words = []

# ->
ZEN = "".join(chr(0xff01 + i) for i in range(94))
HAN = "".join(chr(0x21 + i) for i in range(94))
HAN2ZEN = str.maketrans(HAN, ZEN)

# 
# stopwords = ['', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '']
stopwords = [""]

# 1
for index, row in all_df.iterrows():

    # ->, mecab 
    node = tagger.parseToNode(row[""].translate(HAN2ZEN))

    # 
    while node:
        # 
        features = node.feature.split(',')

        # 1 
        pos1 = features[0]

        # 2 
        pos2 = features[1] if len(features) > 1 else ""

        #  
        base = features[6] if len(features) > 6 else None

        # 
        if base not in stopwords:

            # -
            if (pos1 == "" and pos2 == ""):
                base = base if base is not None else node.surface
                postag = ""
                key = (base, postag)

                # 
                word_counts[key] += 1

                # 
                words.append([index + 1, base, postag, row[""], row[""], key])

            # 
            elif (pos1 == "" and pos2 == ""):
                base = base if base is not None else node.surface
                base = f"{base}"
                postag = ""
                key = (base, postag)

                # 
                word_counts[key] += 1

                # 
                words.append([index + 1, base, postag, row[""], row[""], key])

            # 
            elif pos1 == "":
                base = base if base is not None else node.surface
                postag = ""
                key = (base, postag)

                # 
                word_counts[key] += 1

                # 
                words.append([index + 1, base, postag, row[""], row[""], key])

            # 
            elif pos1 == "":
                base = base if base is not None else node.surface
                postag = ""
                key = (base, postag)

                # 
                word_counts[key] += 1

                # 
                words.append([index + 1, base, postag, row[""], row[""], key])

        # 
        node = node.next

from sklearn.decomposition import LatentDirichletAllocation as LDA

#  LDA 
lda = LDA(max_iter=25, learning_method='batch', random_state=42, n_jobs=-1, n_components=6)
lda.fit(cross_1000_df.values)

# Top 20
n_top_words = 20
feature_names = cross_1000_df.columns
for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(lda.components_):
    print(f"Topic # {topic_idx+1}:", end=" ")
    for i in topic.argsort()[:-n_top_words-1:-1]:
        print(feature_names[i], end=" ")
    print()
